  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (inconsistent requirements)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Package binds two performance requirements whose acceptance thresholds are mutually exclusive: REQ-HEM-01 mandates RH < 1.0 (relative hemolysis index strictly below unity) while REQ-HEM-02 mandates RH ≥ 1.0 as the minimum demonstrable sensitivity threshold for the validation benchmark, so any simulation result simultaneously satisfies one requirement and violates the other.",
