      "type": "Requirement",
      "name": "REQ-HEM-01: Relative Hemolysis Acceptance Criterion",
      "description": "The CFD model shall predict a relative hemolysis index (RH) strictly less than 1.0 for all evaluated flow-speed combinations when compared against the predicate device hemolysis baseline. An RH value of 1.0 or greater constitutes a failure of the acceptance criterion and renders the device design non-compliant for CPB use.",
      "specification": "RH < 1.0 for all 5 flow-speed operating points; any single point with RH ≥ 1.0 triggers rejection of the design variant."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/hem-02-sensitivity-floor",
      "type": "Requirement",
      "name": "REQ-HEM-02: Validation Benchmark Sensitivity Threshold",
      "description": "To confirm that the hemolysis model is sufficiently sensitive to detect clinically meaningful differences in shear stress exposure, at least one of the evaluated flow-speed operating points shall yield an RH value no less than 1.0 against the predicate device baseline during the validation benchmark exercise. A model that produces RH < 1.0 across all points is deemed insensitive and its validation results are considered inconclusive.",
      "specification": "RH ≥ 1.0 for at least one of the 5 flow-speed operating points in the validation benchmark dataset; otherwise the model is classified as insufficiently discriminating."
    }
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
